11 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Safe harbor for compliance in good faith. For the purposes of
12 [sections 1 through 9], an employer who, in good faith, verifies the employment eligibility of a new employee
13 pursuant to the provisions of [sections 1 through 9] is presumed to have complied with all of the provisions of
14 [sections 1 through 9].
15
16 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Prevention of sanctuary policies. A political subdivision of the state
17 may not enact an ordinance or policy, whether written or oral, that limits or otherwise acts in contravention of
18 the attorney general's ability to enforce the provisions of [sections 1 through 9].
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Inapplicability of wrongful discharge of employment provisions. An
21 employer who terminates an employee in order to comply with the provisions of [sections 1 through 9] is not
22 subject to a civil action for wrongful discharge of the employee as provided in Title 39, chapter 2, part 9, or
23 subject to any illegal discrimination claim based in Title 49.
24
